   <h1>Margins and padding</h1>
   <div class = "bigredsquare">
      <p>This paragraph has the default margins and padding.</p>
      <p class = "marginexample">This paragraph has 0.5em margin but no padding. Notice there is 
	                      space outside the border but not inside.</p>
      <p class = "paddingexample">This paragraph has 1em padding but no margin. Notice there is 
	                      space inside the border but not outside.</p>
      <p class = "both">This paragraph has margin and padding.</p>
   </div>	 
	 <div class = "animalsbox">
      This  blue box has:
      <ul>
         <li>top margin of 2.5em. That represents the space above the blue border.</li>
         <li>left padding of 0.8em. Notice the space between the left border and the echidna.</li>
         <li>right margin of 3em. There is space outside the blue border on the right.</li>
         <li>bottom padding of 4.75em: the space under the echidna and inside the border.</li>
      </ul> 

	    <img src = "echidna.jpg" height ="200" width="270" alt = "cute baby" />
